\subsection{Phenomenological exponential fits to $P_S(T)$}

Our semiclassical model does not provide an analytical formula for the decay of coherence shown in Figs.~4b and 5. We perform an exponential fit of the form $A+B\exp(-T/{T_2 ^\mathrm{CPMG}})$ to the data, where $A$ and $B$ account for preparation and readout fidelity and ${T_2 ^\mathrm{CPMG}}$ is a coherence time of the qubit. Typical values of these parameters for fits used to extract values of ${T_2 ^\mathrm{CPMG}}$ shown in Fig.~4c are $A\sim 0.6$ and $B\sim 0.2$. Fit to the data presented in Fig.~5 yields $A=0.53$ and $B=0.34$.










